sin(x)
cos(x)
 \int\frac{1}{\sin^2(x)}dx = -\cot(x) + C 
 \sin^2x = \frac{1 - \cos(2x)}{2} 
 \int\frac{2}{1 - \cos(2x)}dx 
\sin x=\tan x\cos x
\tan x=t.
\begin{align}\int\frac{dx}{\sin^2x}&=\int\frac{1}{\tan^2x}\cdot\frac{dx}{\cos^2x}\\&=\int\frac{1}{t^2}dt\\&=-\frac 1t+C\\&=-\frac{1}{\tan x}+C\\&=-\cot x+C.\end{align}
 \frac{1}{sin x} = csc x 
\int{csc^2 x }
cot x = -csc^2 x
\int{csc^2 x} = - cot x + c
t = \tan \frac{x}{2}
\sin(x)  = \frac{2 t}{1+t^2}
{\rm d}x = \frac{2}{1+t^2}{\rm d} t
 \int \frac{1}{\sin^2 x}\,{\rm d}x = \int \frac{1}{\left(\frac{2 t}{1+t^2}\right)^2} \left( \frac{2}{1+t^2} \right)\,{\rm d}t =\int \frac{1+t^2}{2 t^2}  {\rm d}t = -\frac{1-t^2}{2 t}+C
\sin x = \frac{2 t}{1+t^2}
\cos x = \frac{1-t^2}{1+t^2}
\tan x = \frac{2 t}{1-t^2}
\frac{1-t^2}{2 t} = \frac{\cos x}{\sin x} = \cot x
 \int \frac{1}{\sin^2 x}\,{\rm d}x = -\cot x + C 
